==English==

===Etymology===
{{L.}} '''[[#Latin|constellātiōn]]''', from ''[[con-]]'' “with” and ''[[stella]]'' “star”

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/ˌkɒnstəˈleɪʃǝn/}} {{italbrac|[[RP]]}}
*{{IPA|/ˌkɑnstəˈleɪʃǝn/}} {{italbrac|US}}
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-eɪʃǝn|-eɪʃǝn]]

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
{{en-noun}}

# {{astronomy}}: Any of the 88 officially recognized collections of stars in the night sky.
# An [[arbitrary]] [[formation]] of [[star]]s [[perceived]] as a [[figure]] or [[pattern]].
# An [[image]] associated with a group of stars.
# {{astrology}}: The configuration of [[planet]]s, as used for determining a [[horoscope]].
# {{figurative}} A wide, seemingly [[unlimited]] assortment.
#: ''A '''constellation''' of possibilities.''

